<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="marker">Marker</a> - In the context of <a href="#dna_desoxyribonucleic_acid">DNA</a> assembly, a <a href="#gene">gene</a> that enables the screening or selection of <a href="#bacteria">bacteria</a> containing our desired marker. This could be a <a href="#gene">gene</a> that is toxic to the cell (negative selection; <em>exempli gratia</em> <a href="#ccdb">ccdB</a>), a <a href="#gene">gene</a> that confers antibiotic resistance (positive selection; <em>exempli gratia</em> <a href="#kanamycinResistance">KanR</a>), or a <a href="#gene">gene</a> that turns the bacterial colonies some colour (<em>exempli gratia</em> <a href="#lacz">LacZ</a>, or a <a href="#fluorescence">fluorescent</a> protein such as <a href="#rfp">RFP</a>).